==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[incredibilis]]'', "that cannot be believed".

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|ĭnkrĕ'dəbəl}}, {{IPA|/ɪnˈkrɛdəbəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/In"krEd@b@l/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

# Too [[implausible]] to be [[credible]]; [[beyond belief]]; [[unbelievable]].
#* ''The e-mail she wrote was too '''incredible''' and all her friends thought it was a joke.''
# [[amazing|Amazing]]; [[astonishing]]; [[awe]]-inspiring.
#* ''He was so wrapped up in watching the '''incredible''' special effects that he couldn't keep track of the story.''
# [[marvelous|Marvelous]]; [[profoundly]] affecting; [[wonderful]].
#* ''"Can I see you again? I had such an '''incredible''' experience last night that I simply can't think about anything else."''

